WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:03.481
Previously onLucifer...

00:03.525 --> 00:05.179
LINDA: What do you desire?I want her to choose me.

00:05.222 --> 00:07.268
DAN: I never told you
what I want. I want you.

00:07.311 --> 00:10.184
MAZE: So you thought I wouldn't
find out your mark is fake.

00:10.227 --> 00:12.534
Maybe not tonight,
but I am coming for you.

00:12.577 --> 00:14.840
Neither I nor Lucifer
have the power

00:14.884 --> 00:16.190
to get anyone into Heaven.

00:16.233 --> 00:17.408
I'm going to Hell.

00:17.452 --> 00:18.714
Well, I was hoping
that you might be able

00:18.757 --> 00:19.976
to help me out again.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.674
Any chance to get
in His good graces, I'm in.

00:22.718 --> 00:25.068
I know you're not trying
to freak Chloe out,

00:25.112 --> 00:26.200
but you're getting
in her head.

00:26.243 --> 00:27.897
Let's elope.I can't marry you.

00:27.940 --> 00:30.334
I'm sorry, Marcus.

00:30.378 --> 00:32.597
Oh, no ring.No ring.

00:37.298 --> 00:39.909
♪ Hearts in the cage

00:39.952 --> 00:44.044
♪ Hearts in the cage...

00:44.087 --> 00:45.610
Hey.

00:45.654 --> 00:48.744
You know, I'm really glad
that you told me how you felt.

00:48.787 --> 00:51.486
Oh, I don't know.

00:51.529 --> 00:54.228
All that unresolved
sexual tension?

00:54.271 --> 00:55.664
It was kind of fun.

00:55.707 --> 00:58.449
♪ Never thought that you were

00:58.493 --> 01:03.106
♪ Someone to say things
that you didn't mean ♪

01:03.150 --> 01:06.501
[Ivy and Micah shouting nearby]

01:06.544 --> 01:08.198
[sighs] They're gonna
burn the house down

01:08.242 --> 01:10.635
if we don't get out there.

01:11.636 --> 01:13.160
I made the batter, Dan.

01:13.203 --> 01:14.465
Oh, yeah?

01:14.509 --> 01:16.902
Well, sweet, because the
waffle king has arrived.

01:16.946 --> 01:20.384
Step aside, my lady.

01:20.428 --> 01:22.212
Good morning, Micah.

01:22.256 --> 01:24.519
[grunts]

01:35.573 --> 01:37.880
Thanks for your help.

01:37.923 --> 01:39.316
[gasps]

01:41.188 --> 01:42.667
Hey.

01:42.711 --> 01:44.713
Are you okay?

01:46.323 --> 01:48.325
Is it the same nightmare?

01:50.327 --> 01:53.678
Except this time,
you were in it.

01:58.683 --> 02:00.642
LINDA:
So...

02:00.685 --> 02:02.992
are you going to tell Chloe now?

02:03.035 --> 02:04.515
Tell her what?

02:04.559 --> 02:06.822
Uh, everything.

02:06.865 --> 02:09.129
What we talked about
in your penthouse

02:09.172 --> 02:11.348
before she got engaged?

02:11.392 --> 02:15.352
When you said,
"I want her to choose me."

02:16.353 --> 02:18.312
Right. Yes.

02:18.355 --> 02:19.748
No, no. No need.

02:19.791 --> 02:22.968
She broke it off with Pierce,
so I win.

02:23.012 --> 02:24.187
Yes, I know that they broke up,

02:24.231 --> 02:25.710
but just because
she didn't choose Pierce

02:25.754 --> 02:28.670
doesn't mean she chose you.

02:28.713 --> 02:30.193
And just because
she un-chose Pierce

02:30.237 --> 02:31.977
doesn't not mean
she didn't choose me.

02:32.021 --> 02:33.762
Point is,

02:33.805 --> 02:35.024
no need to rock the boat.

02:35.067 --> 02:36.460
I mean, we all know
how the detective gets

02:36.504 --> 02:37.635
when you push her.

02:37.679 --> 02:39.681
Plus, you know,
she's on the rebound.

02:39.724 --> 02:41.465
Those are excuses.I think

02:41.509 --> 02:45.208
it's best if everyone involved
just goes back to normal.

02:45.252 --> 02:47.993
Easier said than done, Lucifer.

02:48.037 --> 02:50.474
[sighs] Yes, you may be right.

02:51.562 --> 02:53.869
Maybe I should donormal

02:53.912 --> 02:55.479
rather than just say it.

02:55.523 --> 02:57.699
Huh? Help speed things
along a little.

02:57.742 --> 03:00.571
Ah. Another nugget.

03:00.615 --> 03:02.269
Thank you, Doctor.

03:02.312 --> 03:03.879
Yep.

03:03.922 --> 03:05.489
Back to normal.

03:05.533 --> 03:08.144
["Devil on the Run"
by Youth playing]

03:08.188 --> 03:10.190
♪ Your day is gonna come

03:10.233 --> 03:12.975
♪ There's a devil on the run.

03:15.107 --> 03:17.806
Is that really
Forest Clay's wife?

03:17.849 --> 03:19.286
Chloe.

03:19.329 --> 03:21.244
Before you say anything,

03:21.288 --> 03:23.638
I just really want
to apologize for...

03:23.681 --> 03:25.901
the event
that should not be named.

03:25.944 --> 03:27.337
The what?The bachelorette party

03:27.381 --> 03:29.383
from hell.
I-I got caught up.

03:29.426 --> 03:31.428
I acted selfish. Just...Ella, it's fine.

03:31.472 --> 03:32.429
And...[piano playing]

03:32.473 --> 03:34.214
Is that someone playing piano?

03:34.257 --> 03:35.302
I think so.

03:35.345 --> 03:37.391
At a crime scene?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.610
♪

03:44.615 --> 03:46.748
You look familiar. Have we met?

03:46.791 --> 03:47.923
What?

03:47.966 --> 03:51.013
Then you ask
if I like to play cop.

03:51.056 --> 03:52.580
And I say, "No, I like
to play in general,"

03:52.623 --> 03:54.582
Detective, except you were
on the other side of the piano.

03:54.625 --> 03:57.280
That's right, yes. That's
what we said when we first met.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.716
Yeah.What are you doing?

03:58.760 --> 04:01.153
I'm reminding us both
of a life less complicated.

04:01.197 --> 04:02.459
You know, before all that...

04:02.503 --> 04:04.374
Lieutenant-shaped nonsense.

04:04.418 --> 04:06.115
So we can go back to normal.

04:06.158 --> 04:08.770
For example, I'm sure you
remember this little ditty.

04:08.813 --> 04:11.120
[playing "Heart and Soul"]

04:11.163 --> 04:13.122
Come on, take the
top line, Detective.

04:13.165 --> 04:14.297
Don't be shy.

04:14.341 --> 04:16.038
Lucifer. For once,[discordant note plays]

04:16.081 --> 04:17.909
I agree with you,
and I would love nothing more

04:17.953 --> 04:19.389
than for things
to go back to normal.

04:19.433 --> 04:21.086
Oh.

04:21.130 --> 04:23.872
As long as it means
we can get back to work.

04:23.915 --> 04:25.439
Yes, absolutely.

04:25.482 --> 04:27.136
A mystery waits to be solved.

04:27.179 --> 04:28.877
Onwards, Detective.

04:28.920 --> 04:30.966
Oh, anyway,

04:31.009 --> 04:32.881
I just really
want to apologize

04:32.924 --> 04:35.144
for ruining
your engagement, Chloe.

04:35.187 --> 04:36.537
You know,
I-I made it about me

04:36.580 --> 04:39.627
when I should have been
listening to your needs.

04:39.670 --> 04:41.498
You know,
what I need is to move on.

04:41.542 --> 04:43.108
Agreed. There's no point
dwelling in the past,

04:43.152 --> 04:44.632
so let's all move on

04:44.675 --> 04:47.374
by moving even further back,
shall we?

04:47.417 --> 04:49.680
[chuckles] I mean,
they're not breast implants,

04:49.724 --> 04:51.813
but in a pinch...Oh, oh, oh.

04:51.856 --> 04:53.380
No, no, no.
No, no, no. Whoa, whoa!

04:53.423 --> 04:54.642
Whoa... oh!Oh!

04:54.685 --> 04:56.165
No, no, no. Please stop.
Please stop that.

04:56.208 --> 04:57.471
Thank you.Why? What, they're not
evidence, are they?

04:57.514 --> 04:59.516
'Cause I wouldn't be the
carefree rogue of yore

04:59.560 --> 05:00.909
if they weren't.

05:00.952 --> 05:02.214
Not evidence.

05:02.258 --> 05:05.261
Just priceless
historical artifacts.Ooh.

05:05.305 --> 05:09.178
Okay, this baby right here
is from the World Series.

05:09.221 --> 05:11.615
Everyone remembers
Gibson's home run,

05:11.659 --> 05:13.704
but Clay... [spits]

05:13.748 --> 05:16.446
pitched a shutout in Game 2
that was like, boom!

05:17.752 --> 05:19.667
Take that, bitches.

05:19.710 --> 05:21.364
Hmm.

05:21.408 --> 05:24.628
Wait, do you not know
who Forest "King" Clay is?

05:24.672 --> 05:26.456
No idea.Cy Young Award.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.110
World Series MVP.

05:28.153 --> 05:29.851
Beloved American legend?

05:29.894 --> 05:32.462
Is that lock broken?

05:32.506 --> 05:34.856
Ella, you think this
might be a home invasion?

05:34.899 --> 05:36.118
Yeah, I know.

05:36.161 --> 05:37.380
I thought that, too,
but unis said

05:37.424 --> 05:38.860
that it didn't look
like anything was taken.

05:38.903 --> 05:40.383
Was Devon home alone?

05:40.427 --> 05:42.472
No. Forest was here, too,

05:42.516 --> 05:45.083
but medics took him to
the hospital for a head injury.

05:45.127 --> 05:47.216
Apparently the killer
knocked him unconscious.

05:47.259 --> 05:48.043
LUCIFER:
Boom!

05:48.086 --> 05:49.218
Take that, bitches.

05:49.261 --> 05:50.480
CHLOE: Lucifer,
what are you doing?

05:50.524 --> 05:53.353
Oh, right.
You're smoking pot

05:53.396 --> 05:55.398
because you smoked evidence
that one time

05:55.442 --> 05:56.965
next to that suspect's car.

05:57.008 --> 05:58.358
Oh, you remember. Yes.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.011
And the time
at the teen rehab center.

06:00.055 --> 06:02.144
Is it taking you back?
It's taking me, well, somewhere.

06:02.187 --> 06:04.189
Can you...

06:08.629 --> 06:09.978
Guys.

06:10.021 --> 06:11.806
I've got a casing.

06:11.849 --> 06:14.417
Oh, well, that is perfect,
Detective.

06:14.461 --> 06:16.854
My shenanigans
leading to a break in the case?

06:16.898 --> 06:20.205
That is quintessential
Deckerstar.

06:20.249 --> 06:22.425
And the eye roll.
Now you're getting it.

06:23.470 --> 06:25.385
AMENADIEL:
We did it, Charlotte.

06:25.428 --> 06:28.083
We split up
Pierce and Chloe.

06:28.126 --> 06:29.911
Yay.

06:30.955 --> 06:33.088
Sorry. [sighs]

06:33.131 --> 06:35.525
Truth is,
I don't feel any different.

06:35.569 --> 06:37.005
And if Hell is
definitely based

06:37.048 --> 06:39.268
on your own guilt,
then I'm still screwed.

06:39.311 --> 06:41.357
Look, we did a good thing.

06:41.401 --> 06:44.404
And it's important
to celebrate the tiny victories

06:44.447 --> 06:46.493
along the way.Right.

06:46.536 --> 06:49.104
But how will I know
when it's enough,

06:49.147 --> 06:50.540
Amenadiel?

06:50.584 --> 06:52.455
How will you know?

06:52.499 --> 06:53.935
Well, we're very different,
Charlotte.

06:53.978 --> 06:55.458
I'm an angel.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.460
I'll know
when my wings are back.

06:57.504 --> 06:59.288
What about until then?

06:59.331 --> 07:02.944
Aren't you just as mortal
as I am?

07:05.990 --> 07:08.558
Well, I su...
I suppose you're right.

07:09.907 --> 07:12.867
If I were to die
right now, I'm...

07:12.910 --> 07:15.826
I'm not even sure
that I would go to Heaven.

07:15.870 --> 07:17.872
If that's the case,

07:17.915 --> 07:20.396
then there's definitely no hope
for me.

07:20.440 --> 07:23.138
That's where faith comes in,
Charlotte.

07:23.181 --> 07:26.141
Hope in the face
of hopelessness.

07:26.184 --> 07:27.969
But faith?

07:28.012 --> 07:30.754
Angel or not, what I'm hearing

07:30.798 --> 07:33.235
is that you're pretty much
as clueless as I am.

07:33.278 --> 07:36.456
Maybe we're not so
different, after all.

07:40.503 --> 07:42.026
MAN:
My God, it's Forest Clay.

07:42.070 --> 07:44.464
[hushed chatter echoing]

07:47.118 --> 07:48.380
Who's that?

07:48.424 --> 07:50.339
Ah, it's just
some famous athlete

07:50.382 --> 07:51.688
whose wife was killed.

07:56.650 --> 07:58.521
That's Forest Clay.

07:58.565 --> 07:59.783
Oh, I didn't
have you pegged

07:59.827 --> 08:01.002
as a sports fan.

08:01.045 --> 08:02.612
No, from my nightmares.

08:02.656 --> 08:04.005
My Hell loop.

08:05.746 --> 08:08.444
If his wife is dead, he did it.

08:09.489 --> 08:12.187
He's the killer.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.148
♪

08:25.983 --> 08:28.333
I was in the kitchen,

08:28.377 --> 08:31.206
eating leftovers.

08:31.249 --> 08:33.687
I saw a reflection
on the fridge,

08:33.730 --> 08:36.124
and I thought it was Devon.

08:36.167 --> 08:39.083
But when I turned around,
all I saw was...

08:39.127 --> 08:44.132
a gun, a-a mask before
I was hit in the head.

08:44.175 --> 08:47.352
I woke up on
the kitchen floor,

08:47.396 --> 08:49.790
and I ran to Devon.

08:49.833 --> 08:51.835
But she was, uh...

08:54.142 --> 08:56.753
[exhales]
There was so much blood.

08:56.797 --> 08:58.581
I-I...

08:58.625 --> 09:00.235
I couldn't stop the bleeding.

09:00.278 --> 09:02.063
You don't have
to do this right now.

09:02.106 --> 09:04.065
No, I...

09:04.108 --> 09:06.067
I want to.

09:06.110 --> 09:09.418
Did you see anything
that could help identify him?

09:09.461 --> 09:11.072
No.

09:11.115 --> 09:14.771
I don't understand
who would do this to Devon.

09:14.815 --> 09:17.557
CHARLOTTE:
It was him. Forest killed her.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.689
Why do you believe that?13 years ago,

09:19.733 --> 09:21.778
I was an associate
at Wheeler Law.

09:21.822 --> 09:23.606
I'd only been there
for a few months when my boss,

09:23.650 --> 09:26.391
Ben Sr., shows at my place
in the middle of the night.

09:26.435 --> 09:28.045
He handed me a duffel bag.

09:28.089 --> 09:29.090
Told me simply

09:29.133 --> 09:30.439
to incinerate it.

09:30.482 --> 09:32.223
He said it was
for an important client:

09:32.267 --> 09:33.660
Forest Clay.

09:33.703 --> 09:34.791
Well, what was in the bag?

09:34.835 --> 09:36.227
I don't know.

09:36.271 --> 09:38.752
He told me not to open it
or to ask any questions.

09:38.795 --> 09:40.754
And honestly, I didn't want to.

09:40.797 --> 09:42.625
Here's the thing, though.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.627
There was dried blood
on the outside of that bag.

09:44.671 --> 09:46.194
I'm certain of it.

09:46.237 --> 09:47.717
Yes, but it's quite a leap
to thinking

09:47.761 --> 09:49.893
Forest killed someone then
or now, Charlotte.

09:49.937 --> 09:52.592
After years of working
at that firm, I know

09:52.635 --> 09:54.768
how they operate.

09:54.811 --> 09:56.639
Deep down,

09:56.683 --> 09:59.729
I know what I helped cover up
was murder.

09:59.773 --> 10:00.904
I believe her.

10:00.948 --> 10:02.602
Really?

10:02.645 --> 10:04.604
Mm.Why?

10:04.647 --> 10:06.649
Well, which quintessential
response would you like?

10:06.693 --> 10:07.737
The obscure
enigmatic one

10:07.781 --> 10:09.913
or the blunt nonsensical one?

10:09.957 --> 10:11.567
How about the truth.

10:11.611 --> 10:15.049
Well, when Charlotte had her
mini-death, she went to Hell.

10:16.137 --> 10:17.181
Forest haunted her Hell loop

10:17.225 --> 10:18.661
and now is haunting
her nightmares--

10:18.705 --> 10:19.619
which, sidebar,

10:19.662 --> 10:20.968
Dan is also a part of,

10:21.011 --> 10:22.360
so things are heating up there.

10:22.404 --> 10:24.841
[chuckles]:
Oh, well, that sure is nonsense.

10:24.885 --> 10:26.582
Oh, don't worry.
The detective won't believe me.

10:27.627 --> 10:28.845
See? It's classic us.

10:28.889 --> 10:31.413
Look, I know
it sounds far-fetched,

10:31.456 --> 10:34.329
and what Lucifer just said
is flat-out insane.

10:34.372 --> 10:36.113
Eh.CHARLOTTE: Anyway,

10:36.157 --> 10:38.376
if Forest killed someone
13 years ago,

10:38.420 --> 10:41.249
the odds that he killed again
are not unrealistic.

10:41.292 --> 10:44.687
Please, just look into it.

10:44.731 --> 10:46.341
I will do what I always do,

10:46.384 --> 10:49.344
which is investigate
everyone involved.

10:49.387 --> 10:51.607
But until I get a new lead,

10:51.651 --> 10:53.217
I will start with Forest.

10:53.261 --> 10:54.958
Textbook, Detective.

10:55.002 --> 10:56.481
Very good.
[chuckles]

11:02.662 --> 11:05.490
Brother, what are
you doing here?

11:05.534 --> 11:08.406
Personally, I'm avoiding
the, uh, boring forensic part

11:08.450 --> 11:09.886
of the case,
like I normally do.

11:09.930 --> 11:11.453
But you don't day drink.

11:11.496 --> 11:13.324
Something Charlotte
said made me think.

11:13.368 --> 11:15.326
[chuckles]Oh.

11:15.370 --> 11:19.156
Maybe celestial
beings and humans...

11:19.200 --> 11:21.637
Luci, maybe they
aren't that different.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.508
What, are we talking in bed?

11:23.552 --> 11:25.380
'Cause we all know
my skills are preternatural.

11:25.423 --> 11:26.990
But I suppose you,
on the other hand...

11:27.034 --> 11:28.513
I'm talking about the rules
of Heaven and Hell, Luci.

11:28.557 --> 11:31.299
It's all based on
humans' subconscious,

11:31.342 --> 11:32.779
what they think they deserve.

11:32.822 --> 11:35.520
What if that applies
to us as well?

11:35.564 --> 11:37.522
Right. That's enough
for you, drunky.

11:37.566 --> 11:39.524
No, listen.

11:39.568 --> 11:41.396
When I first lost my wings,

11:41.439 --> 11:42.832
I thought Dad was punishing me.

11:42.876 --> 11:46.662
And then I thought
that you were somehow my test,

11:46.706 --> 11:49.665
that in helping God's most
wayward soul, that I would

11:49.709 --> 11:51.754
somehow find redemption.

11:51.798 --> 11:54.278
But, Luci,
I've just been guessing.

11:54.322 --> 11:56.150
Dad never told me any
of those things.

11:56.193 --> 11:58.239
Since when does Dad
ever tell us anything?

11:58.282 --> 12:00.241
That's exactly my point,
brother.

12:00.284 --> 12:03.070
What if He wants us
to judge ourselves?

12:03.113 --> 12:04.332
So my wings,
your wings,

12:04.375 --> 12:06.769
your Devil face...

12:06.813 --> 12:09.293
Brother, what if

12:09.337 --> 12:12.166
we're the ones
who control all of it?

12:12.209 --> 12:13.558
Brother,

12:13.602 --> 12:17.519
that is
absolutely absurd.

12:17.562 --> 12:19.913
Dad holds the reins.
End of story.

12:19.956 --> 12:21.436
Because if we
do have control,

12:21.479 --> 12:23.743
why don't you just pop
your wings out right now?

12:23.786 --> 12:25.875
Hmm? Excuse me.

12:25.919 --> 12:28.051
We might need some room here.
Go on. Be an angel.

12:28.095 --> 12:29.270
Listen, I'm not sure.

12:29.313 --> 12:31.794
I-I still haven't figured
that part out.

12:31.838 --> 12:34.101
Well, I'd stop trying
if I were you. It's exhausting.

12:34.144 --> 12:37.278
[scoffs] No, actually,
on second thoughts,

12:37.321 --> 12:39.889
ponder needlessly, 'cause it's
what you normally do, isn't it?

12:39.933 --> 12:41.586
[chuckles]

12:45.373 --> 12:47.027
♪

12:47.070 --> 12:49.507
♪ So she could never choose.

12:49.551 --> 12:50.944
DAN: No financial scandals,

12:50.987 --> 12:52.728
no personal accusations.

12:52.772 --> 12:55.470
The only nefarious thing Forest
ever did was steal a base.

12:55.513 --> 12:57.254
This guy's as squeaky
clean as they come.

12:57.298 --> 12:58.516
ELLA:
Well, someone is

12:58.560 --> 12:59.822
a dirty little liar.

12:59.866 --> 13:01.737
I was checking out
Forest's medical report,

13:01.781 --> 13:03.478
and something didn't add up.

13:03.521 --> 13:05.349
He said that the killer knocked
him out with a gun, right?

13:05.393 --> 13:06.350
Yeah.

13:06.394 --> 13:09.440
Well, bam!

13:09.484 --> 13:11.138
Or should I say,

13:11.181 --> 13:13.227
no bam?

13:13.270 --> 13:15.055
Hmm?
If a cut

13:15.098 --> 13:17.405
is caused by a blunt object,

13:17.448 --> 13:20.147
there's a presence of tissue
bridging within the wound.

13:20.190 --> 13:21.844
Plus, there'd be
pretty major bruising

13:21.888 --> 13:24.064
if it was caused by something
that knocked him unconscious.

13:24.107 --> 13:26.849
But there was neither.So what caused the wound?

13:26.893 --> 13:29.069
That right there, my friend,
is an incised cut

13:29.112 --> 13:30.418
caused
by something sharp.

13:30.461 --> 13:32.942
Bottom line,
Mr. Clay's nose

13:32.986 --> 13:34.857
is as long as a Dodger Dog.

13:34.901 --> 13:37.164
He lying.

13:37.207 --> 13:40.341
Maybe Charlotte
is onto something.

13:40.384 --> 13:42.212
♪

13:46.086 --> 13:47.391
Careful, Mr. Clay.

13:47.435 --> 13:51.352
Physical activity may not
be wise after, you know,

13:51.395 --> 13:52.396
being hit on the head.

13:52.440 --> 13:53.528
Detective, hi.

13:53.571 --> 13:55.051
What's this about?

13:55.095 --> 13:56.923
Well, Forensics looked
through your medical report.

13:56.966 --> 13:58.925
You weren't hit
with a gun.

13:58.968 --> 14:00.796
Well, maybe I didn't
see it right.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.537
It happened so fast.
Maybe it was...

14:02.580 --> 14:04.582
Maybe I should just jump
to the old chestnut

14:04.626 --> 14:06.933
where you tell me
what you desire.

14:11.198 --> 14:13.765
I just don't want anyone
to find out.

14:13.809 --> 14:15.289
What, that you killed your wife?

14:15.332 --> 14:17.857
No, no, no. I...
Th-That I wasn't even there.

14:17.900 --> 14:19.554
Ah.

14:21.991 --> 14:24.951
The night of Devon's murder...

14:24.994 --> 14:27.127
I was with someone else.

14:27.170 --> 14:28.650
Ooh. A mistress.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.173
[chuckles]

14:30.217 --> 14:32.001
What was her name?

14:33.002 --> 14:34.177
Mia Hytner.

14:34.221 --> 14:36.005
I bartend at
the West Hills Country Club.

14:36.049 --> 14:38.486
Okay. And is that
how you met Forest?

14:38.529 --> 14:41.445
Yes. He came in a lot, even
though he hardly ever drinks.

14:41.489 --> 14:43.230
Ugh.Anyways,

14:43.273 --> 14:44.231
before I knew it, we were...

14:44.274 --> 14:46.320
Hitting a home run?

14:46.363 --> 14:47.321
Digging into the dugout?

14:47.364 --> 14:49.366
Slamming it out of the park?

14:51.586 --> 14:52.892
So you confirm
that you

14:52.935 --> 14:53.936
and Forest were having an affair

14:53.980 --> 14:55.416
and that he was
at your apartment

14:55.459 --> 14:57.070
the night
that Devon Clay was murdered?

14:57.113 --> 14:58.549
Yes.And how did he hurt

14:58.593 --> 15:00.725
his head?Things can get
a little...

15:00.769 --> 15:02.423
wild...

15:02.466 --> 15:04.599
in bed with us sometimes.

15:04.642 --> 15:07.167
That night,
Forest fell

15:07.210 --> 15:08.385
onto the nightstand,

15:08.429 --> 15:10.039
and he shattered the lamp.

15:10.083 --> 15:13.825
That would explain the sharp
cut that Ella described.

15:13.869 --> 15:15.436
Yes. And
furniture-breaking sex

15:15.479 --> 15:18.569
doesn't exactly fit
with Forest's saintly image.

15:18.613 --> 15:20.397
And explain why he
lied about it.
Mm.

15:20.441 --> 15:21.964
MIA:
Try not to judge Forest

15:22.008 --> 15:23.096
too harshly.

15:23.139 --> 15:24.010
He wasn't the first

15:24.053 --> 15:25.707
to cheat on his marriage.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.578
He would never tell you this,

15:27.622 --> 15:30.973
but Devon had been having an
affair with her CEO for years.

15:31.017 --> 15:33.671
Was she, now?

15:33.715 --> 15:35.543
Thank you.
Thank you.

15:41.897 --> 15:44.334
♪

16:01.656 --> 16:03.614
Only one way to sneak up
on a demon:

16:03.658 --> 16:05.703
let her think
she's sneaking up on you.

16:05.747 --> 16:07.357
You see, I knew

16:07.401 --> 16:09.925
it was only a matter of time
before you found my new digs.

16:09.969 --> 16:10.708
Killing me

16:10.752 --> 16:12.188
won't send you home.

16:13.233 --> 16:14.886
Keep talking.

16:14.930 --> 16:16.758
The only way you
can get to Hell

16:16.801 --> 16:18.107
is if Lucifer flies you down.

16:18.151 --> 16:19.369
And the only way he'll do that

16:19.413 --> 16:20.718
is if we destroy his life
on Earth.

16:20.762 --> 16:23.025
That's why framing Lucifer
for your murder

16:23.069 --> 16:24.940
was the perfect plan.

16:24.984 --> 16:27.073
Until you weaseled your way
out of it.

16:27.116 --> 16:28.552
Well, I have a new plan.
Or, rather,

16:28.596 --> 16:30.206
same plan, different victim.

16:30.250 --> 16:32.078
Who's the new sacrificial lamb?

16:32.121 --> 16:34.558
God's favorite son.

16:35.864 --> 16:36.865
[sniffs]

16:39.433 --> 16:41.043
You want me
to kill Amenadiel?

16:41.087 --> 16:42.218
Not exactly.

16:42.262 --> 16:43.872
I want you to bring him to me.

16:43.915 --> 16:44.916
Alive but weakened.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.092
Throw me a soft pitch.

16:46.135 --> 16:47.180
I'll kill him.

16:47.223 --> 16:49.878
You want your mark back.

16:49.921 --> 16:51.053
Exactly.

16:51.097 --> 16:52.533
There's no better way
to piss off God

16:52.576 --> 16:54.883
than killing his favorite
son. I get what I want.

16:54.926 --> 16:56.711
Then we frame Lucifer,
and you get what you want.

16:56.754 --> 16:57.712
It's a win-win.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.018
Why do you need my help

16:59.061 --> 17:00.454
if you're the one
who has to do the killing?

17:00.497 --> 17:02.717
Well, Amenadiel's angelic powers
might be gone,

17:02.760 --> 17:05.024
but he still managed to kill me
nine times when we fought.

17:05.067 --> 17:06.895
Now that I'm mortal...
[chuckles]

17:06.938 --> 17:08.331
there's no do-overs.

17:08.375 --> 17:09.941
I mean, come on,
you're a demon.

17:09.985 --> 17:11.900
He's an angel.
This is what you do.

17:11.943 --> 17:14.511
Unless your time on Earth
changed you more than I thought

17:14.555 --> 17:16.557
and you're not the merciless
badass you used to be.

17:18.950 --> 17:21.953
Nothing's changed.

17:21.997 --> 17:23.129
I'm in.

17:26.132 --> 17:28.134
["Covered Wagon"
by Lo Tom playing]

17:31.833 --> 17:34.444
♪ Don't make me.

17:34.488 --> 17:37.317
♪

17:37.360 --> 17:40.668
Devon was the heart
and soul of King Clay.

17:40.711 --> 17:42.539
I can't tell you
how hard it's been.

17:42.583 --> 17:44.454
[chuckles]
Emphasis on the "hard."

17:44.498 --> 17:46.239
Excuse me?
CHLOE:
We have reason to believe

17:46.282 --> 17:48.632
that you were having an affair
with Devon Clay.

17:48.676 --> 17:49.677
That's crazy.

17:49.720 --> 17:50.939
[chuckles]Look, I get it.

17:50.982 --> 17:52.201
Being with a married woman,

17:52.245 --> 17:53.681
knowing she could
never leave her husband

17:53.724 --> 17:56.205
because of some
stupid company,

17:56.249 --> 17:57.467
his giant face
staring down

17:57.511 --> 17:59.382
at you all day.
I mean, it can be torture

17:59.426 --> 18:01.602
working side by side
with somebody that
you have feelings for.

18:01.645 --> 18:05.388
Especially if you have to deny
those feelings, squash 'em.

18:05.432 --> 18:07.260
You know, it can
be unbearable.

18:07.303 --> 18:08.435
[clears throat]Yeah.

18:08.478 --> 18:10.437
It sounds awful.

18:10.480 --> 18:12.743
But that was not the situation
with me and Devon.

18:12.787 --> 18:14.963
We were just putting in a
lot of hours at the office.

18:15.006 --> 18:17.096
We have to hit the shelves
before the knockoffs do.

18:17.139 --> 18:19.098
Corporate espionage
is a real thing.

18:19.141 --> 18:21.404
Actually caught a spy casing
this place just the other day.

18:21.448 --> 18:23.276
Really? Did you press charges?

18:23.319 --> 18:24.668
Unfortunately, no.
He ran off

18:24.712 --> 18:26.453
when security approached him.Did it occur to you

18:26.496 --> 18:29.064
that he might be stalking
Devon and not your sneakers?

18:29.108 --> 18:31.066
No, God.
Do you think...

18:31.110 --> 18:33.547
I think I'm gonna need to see
all of your security footage.

18:33.590 --> 18:35.766
Yeah. Right this way.

18:35.810 --> 18:36.854
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

18:36.898 --> 18:39.596
♪ Ooh, ooh,
ooh ♪

18:39.640 --> 18:42.077
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh...

18:42.121 --> 18:43.078
Dr. Canaan.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.645
Pleasure.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.082
My office is right this way.

18:47.126 --> 18:49.824
I really hope you
understand just how grave

18:49.867 --> 18:52.000
the incident was.You're in experienced hands.

18:52.043 --> 18:55.351
The firm handles cases like this
all the time.

18:55.395 --> 18:56.613
Really?

18:56.657 --> 18:58.137
Oh, yeah.

18:58.180 --> 19:00.748
How many cases of misdiagnosed
chlamydia are there?

19:00.791 --> 19:03.533
You'd be... surprised?

19:03.577 --> 19:04.708
CHARLOTTE: I'm not
going anywhere.

19:04.752 --> 19:06.623
Get out of my way.Excuse me one moment.

19:06.667 --> 19:08.234
Not until I talk
to Wheeler!

19:08.277 --> 19:09.148
Ben!

19:09.191 --> 19:11.585
Charlotte, what-what's going on?

19:11.628 --> 19:12.716
When I left this firm,

19:12.760 --> 19:14.153
you asked me why.

19:14.196 --> 19:15.328
The truth?

19:15.371 --> 19:16.894
It's because I found out

19:16.938 --> 19:20.724
that there are real consequences
to what you're doing here,

19:20.768 --> 19:22.813
what wedid here.

19:22.857 --> 19:24.337
You tell yourself

19:24.380 --> 19:27.166
that you're defending
the innocent,

19:27.209 --> 19:30.952
upholding some oath,
but you're pretending.

19:30.995 --> 19:32.823
All of you.

19:32.867 --> 19:37.219
Everything you conceal,
every lie you tell,

19:37.263 --> 19:39.526
it adds up.

19:39.569 --> 19:41.702
You're just as guilty

19:41.745 --> 19:44.183
as the criminals
that you represent.

19:44.226 --> 19:45.880
Hell is real.

19:45.923 --> 19:50.406
And, trust me,
all of you are going.

19:50.450 --> 19:53.235
You need help, Charlotte.[scoffs]

19:53.279 --> 19:54.889
And so do I.

19:54.932 --> 19:57.152
Where the hell
is security?

19:57.196 --> 19:58.545
Thank God.

19:58.588 --> 20:01.156
I don't think
God's on your side, Ben.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.853
It may be too
late for us,

20:02.897 --> 20:06.335
but at least
I'm trying to fix things.

20:06.379 --> 20:09.643
[whispers]:
Maybe you can try, too.

20:10.687 --> 20:12.211
[grunts]

20:16.519 --> 20:17.781
Oh.

20:17.825 --> 20:20.262
My apologies for
the interruption, Dr. Canaan.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.177
Shall we continue?

20:22.221 --> 20:25.311
Oh, I'm sorry, but I don't think
this is the firm for me.

20:33.101 --> 20:34.537
Old password still good?

20:34.581 --> 20:36.147
Sure is.

20:40.674 --> 20:42.371
♪

20:42.415 --> 20:43.503
ELLA:
Got him.

20:43.546 --> 20:45.940
Four separate times,
as a matter of fact.

20:45.983 --> 20:48.377
But our facial recognition
software's coming up with squat

20:48.421 --> 20:50.074
because of his hat
and sunglasses.

20:50.118 --> 20:51.859
Average height,

20:51.902 --> 20:54.078
average build,
no visible scars or tattoos.

20:54.122 --> 20:55.863
I mean, even his shoes
are so boring.

20:55.906 --> 20:58.692
Mm, no wonder he's
stealing sneaker secrets.I'll go back

20:58.735 --> 21:00.694
over the footage tonight.
Maybe we missed something.

21:01.738 --> 21:03.697
You Dan Espinoza?

21:03.740 --> 21:05.307
How dare you.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.309
Hey, hey. Actually,
uh, that's for me.

21:07.353 --> 21:08.789
Whew.

21:08.832 --> 21:11.618
Ah. Well, this is
like old times, isn't it?Thanks.

21:11.661 --> 21:13.228
Let me guess,
human head or bomb?

21:13.272 --> 21:14.403
Wager, anyone?

21:14.447 --> 21:15.404
Funny.

21:15.448 --> 21:17.667
No. This is

21:17.711 --> 21:19.321
for...

21:19.365 --> 21:21.889
Charlotte.

21:22.977 --> 21:24.195
Ta-da!

21:24.239 --> 21:26.110
It's a waffle maker.

21:26.154 --> 21:27.764
[sighs]See,

21:27.808 --> 21:29.418
I-I make waffles.

21:29.462 --> 21:31.551
And hers...
uh, iron is really old.

21:31.594 --> 21:33.466
I'm, like, the waffle king?

21:34.467 --> 21:36.469
Is it weird?Very. But I'm glad

21:36.512 --> 21:39.123
to see you're back to your
normal douchey ways, Daniel.

21:39.167 --> 21:42.083
Well, it's between that and...

21:42.126 --> 21:44.041
this.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.348
That's pretty.

21:46.392 --> 21:48.350
It's a waffle.Oh.

21:48.394 --> 21:49.830
That's better, right?It's still weird,

21:49.873 --> 21:52.093
but yes, women tend
to prefer jewelry

21:52.136 --> 21:53.355
over household appliances.

21:53.399 --> 21:55.357
Not really
sure Lucifer's

21:55.401 --> 21:57.403
the authority
on what women want.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.100
[pats Dan's back]

21:59.143 --> 22:00.797
[closes jewelry case]

22:04.714 --> 22:06.455
CHARLOTTE:
This is amazing. See this?

22:06.499 --> 22:08.283
These are
nondisclosure agreements.

22:08.327 --> 22:10.024
Forest Clay and...

22:10.067 --> 22:11.721
14 different women.

22:11.765 --> 22:13.897
Spanning two decades--
the last, Mia Hytner,

22:13.941 --> 22:15.899
barely a week ago.

22:15.943 --> 22:18.815
Question: how does this
prove that Forest is
the killer, though?

22:18.859 --> 22:21.427
Well, 300, 400 grand a pop--
I mean, no one spends

22:21.470 --> 22:23.907
that kind of money unless
they're trying to cover up

22:23.951 --> 22:25.561
something really bad.

22:26.606 --> 22:27.824
Wait.

22:27.868 --> 22:30.523
Joanne Foles.

22:30.566 --> 22:34.353
June 22, 2005.
That's right around the time

22:34.396 --> 22:36.877
I got rid of the duffel bag.
I remember.

22:36.920 --> 22:38.531
[tapping keyboard]

22:38.574 --> 22:41.621
AMENADIEL: "24-year-old
found strangled in a motel."

22:41.664 --> 22:43.971
No way the timing
is coincidence.

22:44.014 --> 22:45.842
Forest killed that woman,
and the proof of it

22:45.886 --> 22:47.104
was in that duffel bag.Yeah,

22:47.148 --> 22:49.063
but not even one mention
of Forest here.

22:49.106 --> 22:50.064
Yeah, you're right.

22:50.107 --> 22:52.066
I may know that Forest did it,

22:52.109 --> 22:55.591
but I still can't prove it
because of what Idid.Hey, at least

22:55.635 --> 22:58.202
we have the victim's name now--
maybe that's gonna lead us

22:58.246 --> 22:59.595
to some other proof.

22:59.639 --> 23:02.990
Tiny victories, remember?

23:03.033 --> 23:04.208
[knocking]

23:04.252 --> 23:06.297
Hey.
CHARLOTTE:
Dan.

23:07.690 --> 23:08.691
I can come back.

23:08.735 --> 23:10.214
No, no.
I should get going.

23:13.653 --> 23:14.784
[whispers]:
Thank you.

23:18.179 --> 23:19.441
Hi.

23:20.790 --> 23:23.793
[quiet crying, sniffling nearby]

23:26.056 --> 23:28.276
Maze.

23:28.319 --> 23:30.626
What are you doing here?
What's wrong?

23:33.499 --> 23:35.936
Everything.

23:35.979 --> 23:38.591
It's all ruined.

23:38.634 --> 23:41.158
I have no one,
Amenadiel.

23:41.202 --> 23:44.423
And I don't know
how that happened.

23:47.817 --> 23:50.994
Maze, I don't know what
you've been going through,

23:51.038 --> 23:54.389
but it is never too late

23:54.433 --> 23:56.435
to fix things.

23:59.699 --> 24:01.614
You can always

24:01.657 --> 24:04.399
be forgiven-- that
isin your hands.

24:04.443 --> 24:06.270
And, um...

24:06.314 --> 24:08.534
well, for what it's worth,

24:08.577 --> 24:11.145
I will always be
here for you.

24:20.763 --> 24:22.809
Hello.

24:22.852 --> 24:24.245
Hi, Lucifer!

24:24.288 --> 24:26.334
Oh, perfect-- you're
exactly where you need to be.

24:26.377 --> 24:28.989
Who is up
for a classic game night, hmm?

24:29.032 --> 24:31.121
Well, actually,
it's a school night for her,

24:31.165 --> 24:33.167
and I was just about to go over

24:33.210 --> 24:34.951
the King Clay
security footage.Remember, all work

24:34.995 --> 24:37.476
and no play makes
the detective... a shoe.

24:39.086 --> 24:40.130
Lucifer?Hmm?

24:40.174 --> 24:41.610
This is... this is
a little weird.

24:41.654 --> 24:43.482
Well, if by "weird,"
you mean you're transported

24:43.525 --> 24:46.485
to a simpler, happier time,
then agreed.

24:46.528 --> 24:48.487
[chuckles]

24:48.530 --> 24:50.967
Uh, no, no, no, I'm afraid
that won't do-- you landed

24:51.011 --> 24:53.535
on the little question mark
last time, so come on, do over.

24:53.579 --> 24:57.234
Mom's right, this isweird--
we can't play

24:57.278 --> 25:00.063
the exact same game
as we did before, Lucifer.

25:00.107 --> 25:01.543
It's not fun.

25:01.587 --> 25:03.023
Isn't it?

25:03.066 --> 25:04.198
Sorry, but...

25:04.241 --> 25:05.982
I should finish
my book report.

25:06.026 --> 25:07.984
Yes, and Ishould
get back to work.

25:08.028 --> 25:10.987
But don't you want to paint
a unicorn on my cheek?
Ugh.

25:11.031 --> 25:11.945
Well, hold on, wait.

25:11.988 --> 25:13.903
Um...There we go.

25:13.947 --> 25:15.426
["Only You" by Yazoo playing]

25:15.470 --> 25:17.254
Okay. What?Come here. Come here.

25:17.298 --> 25:18.299
Lucifer!

25:18.342 --> 25:19.909
What are you doing?

25:19.953 --> 25:21.084
Here we go.

25:21.128 --> 25:23.478
♪ Can you hear me?

25:23.522 --> 25:24.697
[chuckles]

25:24.740 --> 25:26.002
Wait.

25:26.046 --> 25:27.613
[turns off song]Lucifer, stop.

25:27.656 --> 25:29.658
You liked this before,
didn't you?

25:29.702 --> 25:31.921
Yes. I did.

25:31.965 --> 25:33.488
It...

25:33.532 --> 25:35.882
it meant a lot to me, actually,

25:35.925 --> 25:39.059
which is why I don't understand
why you're doing this.

25:40.582 --> 25:42.453
Are you making fun of us?

25:42.497 --> 25:46.022
No. No, I'm trying to remind us
of how great we are together,

25:46.066 --> 25:47.981
to help us get back to normal.

25:48.024 --> 25:49.504
Right.

25:49.548 --> 25:52.942
Well, uh, you know,
I thought I wanted that, too,

25:52.986 --> 25:54.335
but...

25:54.378 --> 25:55.771
maybe we can't.

25:55.815 --> 25:57.860
Or at least maybe Ican't.

25:57.904 --> 25:59.340
[sighs]:
Look...

25:59.383 --> 26:01.081
right now,

26:01.124 --> 26:03.649
normal, it just hurts.

26:03.692 --> 26:05.781
Detective...

26:05.825 --> 26:08.392
I-I think you should go.

26:14.964 --> 26:16.444
Hey, I got something.

26:16.487 --> 26:17.793
You do?Yeah.

26:17.837 --> 26:19.316
Okay, I cross-referenced

26:19.360 --> 26:21.014
the times the suspect
went to King Clay

26:21.057 --> 26:22.276
with Devon's schedule.

26:22.319 --> 26:24.931
Two of the four days,
Devon wasn't even there.

26:24.974 --> 26:26.454
But guess who was.

26:26.497 --> 26:28.717
Forest Clay?All four times

26:28.761 --> 26:31.154
the skulker was there--
right on Forest's heels.

26:31.198 --> 26:33.766
So what if Forest was
the intended target all along?

26:33.809 --> 26:36.246
What if, what if Devon
just got shot by mistake?

26:36.290 --> 26:38.074
Wow.

26:38.118 --> 26:40.120
That is a great theory.[typing rapidly]

26:40.163 --> 26:43.036
Yeah.Uh, are you okay?

26:43.079 --> 26:44.298
Yeah.

26:44.341 --> 26:45.647
Yeah.

26:45.691 --> 26:47.518
Well, I...
I couldn't sleep last night,

26:47.562 --> 26:50.347
so I stayed up all night
working, and, you know,

26:50.391 --> 26:52.741
I drank a lot of caffeine.
Like, a lot.

26:52.785 --> 26:55.135
Was it because
of Pierce?
[sighs]

26:56.919 --> 26:58.573
No.

26:58.617 --> 27:01.924
No. I... I don't think
any of this

27:01.968 --> 27:04.187
is really about Pierce.

27:04.231 --> 27:08.148
I think if I'm honest
with myself...

27:08.191 --> 27:10.977
all of this is about Lucifer.

27:11.020 --> 27:13.457
Lucifer's the...
the reason

27:13.501 --> 27:15.459
that I said yes
to Pierce, and...

27:15.503 --> 27:18.071
he's also the reason
that I said no.

27:18.114 --> 27:20.813
Wow,again.

27:22.423 --> 27:24.599
I'm just so sorry
that I got wrapped up

27:24.643 --> 27:26.601
in the whole idea
of beautiful "Pecker" babies

27:26.645 --> 27:29.386
that I forgot
to check in with you.

27:29.430 --> 27:32.607
Like... like,
reallycheck in with you.

27:32.651 --> 27:33.869
Ella, it's okay.Tell me

27:33.913 --> 27:35.784
what I can do for you right now.

27:35.828 --> 27:38.047
Uh, you can help me
focus on work.

27:38.091 --> 27:39.396
You got it.Okay.

27:39.440 --> 27:43.357
So, if Forest was the
killer's actual target,

27:43.400 --> 27:45.054
what's the motive?

27:45.098 --> 27:46.534
I think I know.

27:46.577 --> 27:48.971
That's A.J. Agholor.

27:49.015 --> 27:50.973
In 2005, he went to jail

27:51.017 --> 27:52.845
for the murder of Joanne Foles.

27:52.888 --> 27:54.150
But A.J.
didn't do it.

27:54.194 --> 27:57.632
Forest did.
A.J.'s motive was revenge.

27:57.676 --> 27:59.373
How did you figure
all of this out?

27:59.416 --> 28:02.158
This is a list of women
that Forest paid off
for the last 20 years.

28:02.202 --> 28:03.899
And look.

28:03.943 --> 28:08.034
Joanne signed
a $300,000 NDA on June 22.

28:08.077 --> 28:10.253
She was killed
on June 25,

28:10.297 --> 28:12.734
the same night I got the bag.CHLOE: Charlotte,

28:12.778 --> 28:14.344
this could all be a
bunch of coincidences,

28:14.388 --> 28:16.216
especially to a jury full
of Forest Clay fans.

28:16.259 --> 28:19.175
Yes, but a lot of coincidences
is a pattern.

28:19.219 --> 28:20.786
And here's the kicker.

28:20.829 --> 28:23.832
A.J. got out of prison
just three weeks ago.

28:23.876 --> 28:25.791
Motive and opportunity.

28:25.834 --> 28:27.314
It all fits.

28:27.357 --> 28:29.882
All right.
We got to find this guy.

28:29.925 --> 28:31.884
♪

28:41.110 --> 28:42.982
Where's Amenadiel?

28:43.025 --> 28:45.375
I decided you were wrong.

28:45.419 --> 28:47.900
Killing Amenadiel won't
get your mark back.

28:47.943 --> 28:49.640
God isn't a drive-thru--

28:49.684 --> 28:51.773
you can't just order
what you want.

28:51.817 --> 28:53.775
No.

28:53.819 --> 28:57.257
You chickened out.
Gone soft, like I thought.

28:57.300 --> 28:58.824
Know what?
I'll do it myself.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.741
Where do you think
you're going?

29:03.829 --> 29:05.700
[grunting]

29:09.008 --> 29:11.488
How's that for soft?

29:13.229 --> 29:16.189
CHLOE: We found this
in your car, A.J.

29:16.232 --> 29:19.366
It matches the casing that was
found next to Devon Clay's body.

29:19.409 --> 29:22.412
Now, I don't think you
meant to kill Devon.

29:22.456 --> 29:25.720
I don't. I think that you
were following Forest for weeks,

29:25.764 --> 29:29.158
you broke into his house
when you knew he'd be home
alone, only he wasn't--

29:29.202 --> 29:30.594
Devon surprised you.
You panicked,

29:30.638 --> 29:32.161
and you shot her.

29:32.205 --> 29:34.207
You've been in prison
for 13 years

29:34.250 --> 29:37.253
for a crime you
didn't commit.

29:37.297 --> 29:39.995
It's understandable that
you would want revenge.

29:40.039 --> 29:42.432
Yeah. But not for me.

29:42.476 --> 29:45.218
For Joanie.

29:45.261 --> 29:48.134
We were gonna get married.
She broke it off.

29:48.177 --> 29:49.962
For Forest?Yeah.

29:50.005 --> 29:52.529
Only she didn't tell me
that was his name back then.

29:52.573 --> 29:53.704
She was too scared.

29:53.748 --> 29:54.531
Scared?

29:54.575 --> 29:56.664
He used to hurt her.

29:57.752 --> 29:59.885
She said she
was gonna leave him.

29:59.928 --> 30:03.889
Then one night,
she calls me crying, screaming.

30:03.932 --> 30:07.196
Next thing I knew,
I'm going down for murder.

30:07.240 --> 30:09.851
When did you find out
that it was Forest?When I got out of jail,

30:09.895 --> 30:11.766
I went to go see Joanie's mom.

30:11.810 --> 30:14.464
She told me that's who Joanie
was dating when she died.

30:14.508 --> 30:17.990
Did she, or you,
have any proof?

30:18.033 --> 30:19.034
Mm-mm.

30:19.078 --> 30:20.427
CHARLOTTE:
Damn.

30:20.470 --> 30:22.472
More hearsay.

30:22.516 --> 30:24.213
Ah, Charlotte.

30:28.957 --> 30:30.176
Who's that?

30:30.219 --> 30:32.178
He killed Devon Clay.

30:32.221 --> 30:33.744
Long story.

30:33.788 --> 30:36.835
So the detective
caught the bad guy.

30:36.878 --> 30:38.488
Without me.

30:38.532 --> 30:40.186
CHLOE:
All right, thank you.

30:40.229 --> 30:42.405
Yeah, he's not the
realbad guy.

30:44.668 --> 30:46.409
Thank you.

30:46.453 --> 30:49.021
I know you're gonna say
there's still no proof.

30:49.064 --> 30:50.413
No, I wanted to
say thank you.

30:50.457 --> 30:52.589
Thank you for helping
me solve this case.

30:52.633 --> 30:55.636
And I might have an idea
of how to solve yours.

30:59.422 --> 31:00.510
[Maze yells]

31:00.554 --> 31:02.295
[groaning]

31:07.430 --> 31:08.779
[grunting]

31:11.043 --> 31:13.349
Okay. Time out. Time out.

31:13.393 --> 31:15.874
Geez. I won't
go after Amenadiel.

31:15.917 --> 31:18.398
You won't?You're probably right--
it wouldn't work anyway.

31:35.981 --> 31:37.112
[groans]

31:37.156 --> 31:39.071
[blade scrapes]

31:39.114 --> 31:40.855
[yells]

31:40.899 --> 31:43.945
I hadto kill you before,
but now I just wantto.

31:43.989 --> 31:46.817
Okay, you could kill me, sure,
but Linda would die, too.

31:46.861 --> 31:49.298
You're full of it.Maybe I knew you
weren't gonna follow through,

31:49.342 --> 31:50.647
so I needed a fail-safe.

31:50.691 --> 31:51.822
Liar!

31:51.866 --> 31:55.217
Call her. Tell her
to look out her window.

31:58.307 --> 31:59.439
[both grunt]

32:00.570 --> 32:02.311
